content.text:
The root cause of the false positive with "else if" is the logic in `MultiLineIfElseRule.beforeVisitChildNodes`. 

The code tries to allow a single-line `else if (...)` only if the "else if" appears entirely on one line (i.e., there's no newline before `else`). This doesn't account for legitimate multiline usages of "else if" which should *not* be forcibly rewritten into `else { if }` blocks.

**Current check:**
```kotlin
if (!node.treePrev.textContains('\n')) {
    if (node.firstChildNode.elementType == IF) {
        // Allow single line for:
        // else if (...)
        return
    }
    // ... other conditions
}
```
This restricts multiline-else-if patterns.

**To fix this:**

We want to allow `else if` branches (regardless of line breaks) to remain as-is, matching Kotlin conventions. So, if the first child of an `ELSE` node is an `IF`, we should *always* allow it without block insertion, not only for single-line cases.

---

**Proposed code change:**

Change this part:
```kotlin
if (!node.treePrev.textContains('\n')) {
    if (node.firstChildNode.elementType == IF) {
        return
    }
    // ...
}
```
to:
```kotlin
if (node.firstChildNode.elementType == IF) {
    // Always allow else if ( ... ) { ... }
    return
}
// ... existing logic otherwise
```

---

I'll update the file `ktlint-ruleset-standard/src/main/kotlin/com/pinterest/ktlint/ruleset/standard/rules/MultiLineIfElseRule.kt` accordingly.

